==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zither
<hw>Zith"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. <ets>zither</ets>.
See <er>Cittern</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An instrument of
music used in Austria and Germany. It has from thirty to forty wires
strung across a shallow sounding-board, which lies horizontally on a
table before the performer, who uses both hands in playing on it.
<note>[Not to be confounded with the old lute-shaped
<contr>cittern</contr>, or <contr>cithern</contr>.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ziti</ent>⟦br⟧
